reviews.review_text:
Wish I had been there. I kick myself now for not going to one of these Warfield shows in 1980 The acoustic sets have always been my favorite. I always liked Reckoning. I lived in Sacramento and was in my mid 20s at that time so I certainly could of. I didn't like to venture to SF. because of the logistics, parking etc. 
That said this show is great but the recording is not the best especially at the beginning, but it does get better. Lots of base that is for sure. Some of the higher notes cannot be heard at times.It is too bad that Dire wolf the first song of the first set is not here, but
 the show is definitely worth a listen.
